{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Members of this family constitute the solute-binding protein component of cluster-9 ABC transporters. This family includes periplasmic solute binding protein TroA from Treponema pallidum, which binds Zn2+ and Mn2+ [[cite:PUB00078715]]. In Streptococcus suis, TroA is required for manganese acquisition [[cite:PUB00070762]]. Related proteins are found in both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria, including manganese-binding lipoprotein MntA [[cite:PUB00070764]] and high-affinity zinc uptake system protein ZnuA [[cite:PUB00070763]].</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ZnuA is part of the bacterial zinc-uptake complex ZnuABC. ZinT acts as a Zn2+-buffering protein that delivers Zn2+ to ZnuA, a high-affinity zinc-uptake protein. In Gram-negative bacteria the ZnuABC transporter system ensures an adequate import of zinc in Zn2+-poor environments, such as those encountered by pathogens within the infected host [[cite:PUB00075691], [cite:PUB00070763]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "2xy4", "name" "X-RAY STRUCTURE OF ZNUA-WT FROM SALMONELLA ENTERICA"}, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"pfam" {"PF01297" "Zinc-uptake complex component A periplasmic"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Periplasmic solute binding protein, ZnuA-like", "short" "ZnuA-like"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 94, "domain_architectures" 76, "proteomes" 7302, "taxa" 29450, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 56939, "sets" 0, "proteins" 55750, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 42807}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR006127", :literature {"PUB00070762" {"URL" nil, "issue" "19", "authors" ["Wichgers Schreur PJ" "Rebel JM" "Smits MA" "van Putten JP" "Smith HE."], "ISO_journal" "J. Bacteriol.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1128/JB.05305-11", "medline_journal" "J Bacteriol", "title